eriDNXSts1MIB.name: eriDNXSts1MIB
eriDNXSts1MIB.contactinfo: Customer Service Postal: Eastern Research, Inc. 225 Executive Drive Moorestown, NJ 08057 Phone: +1-800-337-4374 Email: support@erinc.com
eriDNXSts1MIB.description: The ERI Enterprise MIB Module for the DNX STS1 Device.

VtGroupType.name: VtGroupType
VtGroupType.description: Indicates the type of Virtual Tributaries (VT) grouping option used on the links. VT 1.5 is used to group T1 links into 7 groups of 4 for the 28 links. VT 2.0 is used to group E1 links into 7 groups of 3 for the 21 links. Using the VT 2.0, links divisible by 4 are skipped over and not used.

sts1MapperConfigTable.name: sts1MapperConfigTable
sts1MapperConfigTable.description: This is the STS-1 Mapper LIU Configuration table which consists of an entry for each of the STS-1 cards. The total number of entries depends on the number of STS-1 cards in the nest.

sts1MapperConfigEntry.name: sts1MapperConfigEntry
sts1MapperConfigEntry.description: The conceptual row of the STS-1 Mapper LIU Configuration table. A row in this table cannot be added or deleted, only modified.

sts1MapperAddr.name: sts1MapperAddr
sts1MapperAddr.description: This number uniquely identifies a STS-1 slot/mapper.

sts1MapperResource.name: sts1MapperResource
sts1MapperResource.description: Uniquely identifies an STS1 Device in the system. This number is provided as key to allow the manager to map this entry to a corresponding Resource Table entry.

sts1VtGroup1.name: sts1VtGroup1
sts1VtGroup1.description: Indicates the type of grouping option used to on links 1 through 4. Using the VT 2.0, link 4 is not used.

sts1VtGroup2.name: sts1VtGroup2
sts1VtGroup2.description: Indicates the type of grouping option used to on links 5 through 8. Using the VT 2.0, link 8 is not used.

sts1VtGroup3.name: sts1VtGroup3
sts1VtGroup3.description: Indicates the type of grouping option used to on links 9 through 12. Using the VT 2.0, link 12 is not used.

sts1VtGroup4.name: sts1VtGroup4
sts1VtGroup4.description: Indicates the type of grouping option used to on links 13 through 16. Using the VT 2.0, link 16 is not used.

sts1VtGroup5.name: sts1VtGroup5
sts1VtGroup5.description: Indicates the type of grouping option used to on links 17 through 20. Using the VT 2.0, link 20 is not used.

sts1VtGroup6.name: sts1VtGroup6
sts1VtGroup6.description: Indicates the type of grouping option used to on links 21 through 24. Using the VT 2.0, link 24 is not used.

sts1VtGroup7.name: sts1VtGroup7
sts1VtGroup7.description: Indicates the type of grouping option used to on links 25 through 28. Using the VT 2.0, link 28 is not used.

sts1VtMapping.name: sts1VtMapping
sts1VtMapping.description: Indicates the Mapper Standard currently in use.

sts1Timing.name: sts1Timing
sts1Timing.description: Indicates whether the STS-1 device uses an internal or external clock source.

sts1ShortCable.name: sts1ShortCable
sts1ShortCable.description: Indicates the line build out of the STS-1 transmitter. 'enable' when attached to a cable less than 50 feet long.

sts1MaprCmdStatus.name: sts1MaprCmdStatus
sts1MaprCmdStatus.description: The command status for this link configuration row/record. The value used in a SET will be replaced by a response value in the GET RESPONSE indicating success or failure. Default Response State used in GET RESPONSE Command ready-for-command (0) initial default status for a row STS1 Link Commands used in SET Command (1..199) update-link-config(1), Change existing Link Configuration Response States used in GET RESPONSE Command (200..399) update-successful (201) Link data has been successfully changed STS1 Mapper Config Error Codes used in GET RESPONSE Command (400..699) err-general-link-config-error (400) Unknown link configuration error occurred err-invalid-link-status (401) Unrecognized link status setting err-invalid-link-framing (402) Line framing type not valid for link type err-invalid-link-command (403) Unrecognized link command-action err-invalid-link-op-mode (407) Configured M13 Op mode not valid for port; verify other link parameters match desired new mode err-invalid-link-rem-loop (408) Remote Loop type not valid for sts1 frame type err-invalid-link-ais (409) Unrecognized sts1 AIS selection err-data-locked-by-another-user (450) Another administrative user is making changes to this part of the system via a terminal session. Check Event Log for user name err-snmp-parse-failed (500) Agent could not parse variable err-invalid-snmp-type (501) Variable ASN type does not match Agent defined type err-invalid-snmp-var-size (502) Variable size is too big

sts1T1E1LinkConfigTable.name: sts1T1E1LinkConfigTable
sts1T1E1LinkConfigTable.description: This is the STS T1/E1 Link Configuration table which consists of an entry for each of the card's 28 links. The total number of entries depends on the number of STS1 cards in the nest.

sts1T1E1LinkConfigEntry.name: sts1T1E1LinkConfigEntry
sts1T1E1LinkConfigEntry.description: The conceptual row of the STS T1/E1 Link Configuration table. A row in this table cannot be added or deleted, only modified.

sts1T1E1CfgLinkAddr.name: sts1T1E1CfgLinkAddr
sts1T1E1CfgLinkAddr.description: This number uniquely identifies a STS T1/E1 link resource. This number will be used throughout the system to identify a unique resource.

sts1T1E1CfgResource.name: sts1T1E1CfgResource
sts1T1E1CfgResource.description: Uniquely identifies an STS T1/E1 Channel in the system. This number is provided as key to allow the manager to map this entry to a corresponding Resource Table entry.

sts1T1E1CfgLinkName.name: sts1T1E1CfgLinkName
sts1T1E1CfgLinkName.description: This is the user friendly text name to identify the link.

sts1T1E1Status.name: sts1T1E1Status
sts1T1E1Status.description: Dictates the current status of the link, in-service or out-of-service.

sts1T1E1Clear.name: sts1T1E1Clear
sts1T1E1Clear.description: Determines if the port supports T1 or E1 unframed.

sts1T1E1Framing.name: sts1T1E1Framing
sts1T1E1Framing.description: Determines the type of framing used on the line. Choose between T1 SuperFrame 'D4', Extended SuperFrame (ESF), or T1 Unframed. Currently E1 is not supported. When value of sts1T1E1Clear is set to unframed (2), the only valid framing options are: e1Unframed(4) or t1Unframed(7).

sts1T1E1NetLoop.name: sts1T1E1NetLoop
sts1T1E1NetLoop.description: Determines whether or not the module should respond to loop diagnostic commands received from the network supplier. Select 'enable' unless the commands are to be passed to another STS1 device.

sts1T1E1YelAlrm.name: sts1T1E1YelAlrm
sts1T1E1YelAlrm.description: Causes the module to discard data and send a yellow alarm if it is in a red alarm condition after a 3 second period. 'Yes' must be chosen if the network supplier is a common carrier, such as a telephone company.

sts1T1E1RecoverTime.name: sts1T1E1RecoverTime
sts1T1E1RecoverTime.description: This is the red alarm timeout value. Determines the amount of seconds the port will wait to stop sending the yellow alarm when coming out of a red alarm condition.

sts1T1E1EsfFormat.name: sts1T1E1EsfFormat
sts1T1E1EsfFormat.description: Determines the type of ESF network commands the T-1 link will respond to. It has no meaning for D4 networks. With ESF networks, this information must be obtained from the network supplier.

sts1T1E1IdleCode.name: sts1T1E1IdleCode
sts1T1E1IdleCode.description: Determines the whether the code that will be transmitted over the unused links will be 'idle' or 'busy' (all 1's).

sts1T1E1CfgCmdStatus.name: sts1T1E1CfgCmdStatus
sts1T1E1CfgCmdStatus.description: The command status for this link configuration row/record. The value used in a SET will be replaced by a response value in the GET RESPONSE indicating success or failure. Default Response State used in GET RESPONSE Command ready-for-command (0) initial default status for a row STS1-T1 Link Commands used in SET Command (1..199) update(1) Change existing Link Configuration inServiceAll (7) Change Link Status to in-service for all 8 links. copyToAll (9) Copy T1 Link configuration to all other links within the same device outOfServiceAll (12) Change Link Status to out-of-service for all 8 links. Response States used in GET RESPONSE Command (100..199) update-successful (101) Link data has been successfully changed insvc-successful (107) All Links have been successfully placed In Service copy-successful (109) T1 Link data has been successfully copied to other links oos-successful (112) All Links have been successfully placed Out of Service STS1-T1 Link Config Error Codes used in GET RESPONSE Command (400..699) err-general-link-config-error (400) Unknown link configuration error occurred err-invalid-link-status (401) Unrecognized link status setting err-invalid-link-framing (402) Line framing type not valid for link type err-invalid-link-command (403) Unrecognized link command-action err-invalid-esf-format (405) ESF type not applicable to link type err-invalid-link-density (406) Unrecognized T1 link density setting err-invalid-network-loop (410) Unrecognized network loop setting err-invalid-yellow-alrm (411) Unrecognized yellow alarm setting err-invalid-red-timeout (412) Unrecognized red alarm timeout err-invalid-idle-code (413) Unrecognized idle code err-device-in-standby (414) Can't change config for designated Standby device err-data-locked-by-another-user (450) Another administrative user is making changes to this part of the system via a terminal session. Check Event Log for user name err-snmp-parse-failed (500) Agent could not parse variable err-invalid-snmp-type (501) Variable ASN type does not match Agent defined type err-invalid-snmp-var-size (502) Variable size is too big

sts1T1E1Gr303Facility.name: sts1T1E1Gr303Facility
sts1T1E1Gr303Facility.description: Enables link to be configured as a Gr303 Facility

sts1MapperStatusTable.name: sts1MapperStatusTable
sts1MapperStatusTable.description: This is the STS-1 Mapper Status table which consists of a single entry for each card's Mapper Display. The total number of entries depends on the number of STS1 cards in the node.

sts1MapperStatusEntry.name: sts1MapperStatusEntry
sts1MapperStatusEntry.description: The conceptual row of the Mapper table. A row in this table cannot be added or deleted, only modified.

sts1MapperStatusAddr.name: sts1MapperStatusAddr
sts1MapperStatusAddr.description: This number uniquely identifies a STS1 Mapper resource. This number will be used throughout the system to identify a unique resource.

sts1MapperStatusResource.name: sts1MapperStatusResource
sts1MapperStatusResource.description: This number uniquely identifies a STS1 Mapper resource. This number is provided as key to allow the manager to map this entry to a corresponding Resource Table Entry.

sts1MapperStatusState.name: sts1MapperStatusState
sts1MapperStatusState.description: Determines the current line condition status of the Mapper. ok (0), lof (32), -- bit 5 lop (256), -- bit 8 oof (512), -- bit 9 ais (1024), -- bit 10 los (8192), -- bit 13 lomf (131072), -- bit 17 errors (2147483647) -- all

sts1MapperStatusLOSErrs.name: sts1MapperStatusLOSErrs
sts1MapperStatusLOSErrs.description: This is the number of seconds a Loss of Signal was declared.

sts1MapperStatusOOFErrs.name: sts1MapperStatusOOFErrs
sts1MapperStatusOOFErrs.description: This is the number of seconds an Out Of Frame alignement error was declared.

sts1MapperStatusLOFErrs.name: sts1MapperStatusLOFErrs
sts1MapperStatusLOFErrs.description: This is the number of seconds a Loss of Frame was declared.

sts1MapperStatusLOPtrErrs.name: sts1MapperStatusLOPtrErrs
sts1MapperStatusLOPtrErrs.description: This is the number of seconds a Loss of Pointer was declared.

sts1MapperStatusAISErrs.name: sts1MapperStatusAISErrs
sts1MapperStatusAISErrs.description: This is the number of seconds an Alarm Indication Signal was declared.

sts1MapperStatusMultiFErrs.name: sts1MapperStatusMultiFErrs
sts1MapperStatusMultiFErrs.description: This is the number of seconds a Near End Loss of Multi-Frame Signal was declared.

sts1MapperStatusRxTraceErrs.name: sts1MapperStatusRxTraceErrs
sts1MapperStatusRxTraceErrs.description: This is the number of seconds an error has been detected in the receive path trace.

sts1MapperStatusTotErrSecs.name: sts1MapperStatusTotErrSecs
sts1MapperStatusTotErrSecs.description: This is the total number of Errored Seconds.

sts1MapperStatusCmdStatus.name: sts1MapperStatusCmdStatus
sts1MapperStatusCmdStatus.description: This is the command status for the Mapper Row. The value used in a SET will be replaced by a response value in the GET RESPONSE indicating success or failure. Default Response State used in GET RESPONSE Command ready-for-command (0) initial default status for a row Action Commands used in SET Command (1..99) update (1) Can be used optionally when activating loops and berts in order to get status code back in response clearErrors (14) Resets all error counters to zero Response States used in GET RESPONSE Command (100..199) update-successful (101) Test action has been successfully performed clear-successful (114) Error counts have been successfully cleared The Error Codes used in GET RESPONSE Command (200..799) err-general-test-error (200) Unknown Test request error occurred. err-field-cannot-be-set (206) Read-only field was included in SET request err-snmp-parse-failed (500) Agent could not parse variable err-invalid-snmp-type (501) Variable ASN type does not match Agent defined type err-invalid-snmp-var-size (502) Variable size is too big

sts1LIUTable.name: sts1LIUTable
sts1LIUTable.description: This is the STS1 LIU Diagnostic Status table which consists of an entry for each STS1 card's Line Interface Unit Display. The number of entries depends on the number of STS1 cards in the node.

sts1LIUEntry.name: sts1LIUEntry
sts1LIUEntry.description: The conceptual row of the Mapper table. A row in this table cannot be added or deleted, only modified.

sts1LIUAddr.name: sts1LIUAddr
sts1LIUAddr.description: This number uniquely identifies a STS1 Mapper resource address. This number will be used throughout the system to identify a unique resource.

sts1LIUResource.name: sts1LIUResource
sts1LIUResource.description: This number uniquely identifies a STS1 Mapper resource. This number is provided as a key to allow the manager to map this entry to a corresponding Resource Table Entry.

sts1LIUBertState.name: sts1LIUBertState
sts1LIUBertState.description: This is the LIU Bert State indicated by on/off.

sts1LIUBertErrSecs.name: sts1LIUBertErrSecs
sts1LIUBertErrSecs.description: This is the number of LIU Bert Errored seconds.

sts1LIUBertDuration.name: sts1LIUBertDuration
sts1LIUBertDuration.description: This is the number of seconds for the LIU Bert Duration.

sts1LIULoopType.name: sts1LIULoopType
sts1LIULoopType.description: Indicates the loopback status of the Mapper/LIU for this STS1 device. off (0) - indicates loopback is disabled mapper (1) - indicates Mapper local data is looped back to itself liu (39)- indicates Line Interface Unit local data is looped back to itself.

sts1LIUDigitalErrs.name: sts1LIUDigitalErrs
sts1LIUDigitalErrs.description: This is the number of seconds recorded for the LIU Digital Errors.

sts1LIUAnalogErrs.name: sts1LIUAnalogErrs
sts1LIUAnalogErrs.description: This is the number of seconds recorded for the LIU Analog Errors.

sts1LIUExcessZeros.name: sts1LIUExcessZeros
sts1LIUExcessZeros.description: This is the number of seconds LIU Excess zero errors were detected.

sts1LIUCodingViolationErrs.name: sts1LIUCodingViolationErrs
sts1LIUCodingViolationErrs.description: This is the total number of Errored Seconds for the LIU Coding Violation.

sts1LIUPRBSErrs.name: sts1LIUPRBSErrs
sts1LIUPRBSErrs.description: This is the total number of Errored Seconds for the LIU PRBS check.

sts1LIUCmdStatus.name: sts1LIUCmdStatus
sts1LIUCmdStatus.description: This is the command status for the LIU Mapper Row. The value used in a SET will be replaced by a response value in the GET RESPONSE indicating success or failure. Default Response State used in GET RESPONSE Command ready-for-command (0) initial default status for a row LIU Action Commands used in SET Command (1..99) update (1) Can be used optionally when activating loops and berts in order to get status code back in response clearErrors (14) Resets all error counters and bert test time to zero Response States used in GET RESPONSE Command (100..199) update-successful (101) Test action has been successfully performed clear-successful (114) Error counts have been successfully cleared LIU Test Error Codes used in GET RESPONSE Command (200..799) err-general-test-error (200) Unknown Test request error occurred. err-invalid-loop-type (202) Unrecognized loop selection err-invalid-bert-type (203) Unrecognized bert selection err-test-in-progress (205) Requested action cannot be performed during bert err-field-cannot-be-set (206) Read-only field was included in SET request err-snmp-parse-failed (500) Agent could not parse variable err-invalid-snmp-type (501) Variable ASN type does not match Agent defined type err-invalid-snmp-var-size (502) Variable size is too big

dnxSTS1Enterprise.name: dnxSTS1Enterprise
dnxSTS1Enterprise.description: ERI DNX STS1 Enterprise for Alarms/Events

sts1MapperConfigTrap.name: sts1MapperConfigTrap
sts1MapperConfigTrap.description: This trap is used to notify a NMS that a user has updated the Link configuration for a given STS1 Mapper entry.

sts1T1E1ConfigTrap.name: sts1T1E1ConfigTrap
sts1T1E1ConfigTrap.description: This trap is used to notify a NMS that a user has updated the Link configuration for a given STS-1 T1 channel entry.
